node.contents: @KshitizSharma what about the server side, could you post that full thread dump as well? Actually I would check first if the H2 server version is the same as the client (in theory it shouldn't be a problem but in the past there were some compatibilities).

astNode.text: @KshitizSharma what about the server side, could you post that full thread dump as well? Actually I would check first if the H2 server version is the same as the client (in theory it shouldn't be a problem but in the past there were some compatibilities).

node.contents: @KshitizSharma Well the TCP server doesn't respond yet, so the client has to wait. Of course there is a timeout. If you know how to solve the problem, patches are welcome :-)

astNode.text: @KshitizSharma Well the TCP server doesn't respond yet, so the client has to wait. Of course there is a timeout. If you know how to solve the problem, patches are welcome :-)

node.contents: @ThomasMueller The problem goes away if I change the database url string to `localhost` instead of `localhost:8082`. I don't understand why this is happening though. Isn't it supposed to run on port 8082?

astNode.text: @ThomasMueller The problem goes away if I change the database url string to `localhost` instead of `localhost:8082`. I don't understand why this is happening though. Isn't it supposed to run on port 8082?

node.contents: @KshitizSharma the default port for the web server is 8082, but that's the wrong server. You don't want to connect to the web server, you want to connect to the TCP server. And there the default port is 9092.

astNode.text: @KshitizSharma the default port for the web server is 8082, but that's the wrong server. You don't want to connect to the web server, you want to connect to the TCP server. And there the default port is 9092.

node.contents: The default port for the web server is 8082, but that's the wrong server. You don't want to connect to the web server, you want to connect to the TCP server. And there the default port is 9092.
